231
00:13:22,558 --> 00:13:24,753
Wonderful. Well, I wanted to talk
to you about a special program...

232
00:13:24,827 --> 00:13:26,761
that we have
for bright students.

233
00:13:26,829 --> 00:13:28,763
- Really ? And he qualifies ?

234
00:13:28,831 --> 00:13:30,822
- Oh, yes. Absolutely.
- Sorry. Excuse me.

235
00:13:30,900 --> 00:13:34,199
- Certainly.
- Because-- when you hear his syntax,

236
00:13:34,270 --> 00:13:36,204
- Hello ? Oh, hi.
- it's amazing.

237
00:13:36,272 --> 00:13:38,502
- Verbal skills are telling.
- His vocabulary is good,
but his syntax is--

238
00:13:38,574 --> 00:13:40,508
- Oh, great.
- He speaks like a grown-up.

239
00:13:40,576 --> 00:13:42,669
- Sorry. Lenny ?
- What we can do is--

240
00:13:42,745 --> 00:13:44,975
- Sorry. Excuse me.
- Oh, certainly.

241
00:13:45,047 --> 00:13:48,539
Can we meet the Dorians tonight
for dinner at Le Cirque ?

242
00:13:48,617 --> 00:13:52,018
The Dorians ? No. Because we have
tickets to the Edward Albee play.

243
00:13:52,088 --> 00:13:55,524
- Listen, I can't.
- We have to.
We've been waiting for so long.

244
00:13:55,591 --> 00:13:58,253
You don't have to go,
but I really should go.

245
00:13:58,327 --> 00:14:00,454
I, uh-- No.

246
00:14:00,529 --> 00:14:03,430
- This will be the second time
this week we cancelled something.
- Go with Bud.

247
00:14:03,499 --> 00:14:06,024
- Oh, okay.
- I don't want to go with Bud.
I'm not married to Bud.

248
00:14:06,102 --> 00:14:08,195
Listen, go.
Can we not discuss it now ?

249
00:14:08,270 --> 00:14:10,738
Oh, my God !
That was embarrassing.

250
00:14:10,806 --> 00:14:14,833
Well, just because I don't
want to have dinner yet again
with the world's dullest couple.

251
00:14:14,910 --> 00:14:17,140
Yeah, well, someday they may
sponsor me for my own gallery.

252
00:14:17,213 --> 00:14:19,147
- I said I'd go. I'm going with you.
- Yeah ?

253
00:14:19,215 --> 00:14:21,149
But we got tickets to a show.
It's a shame.

254
00:14:21,217 --> 00:14:23,981
This time try and join in and don't
sit there like some zombie all night.

255
00:14:24,053 --> 00:14:26,317
Hey, last time I joined in,
you got angry with me.

256
00:14:26,389 --> 00:14:29,688
Yeah, 'cause we were discussing
the l.M. Pei Museum, not Muhammad Ali.

257
00:14:29,759 --> 00:14:33,092
Well, my mind wandered.
I can't keep on those topics.

258
00:14:33,162 --> 00:14:36,962
I just don't want to be the motor power
of the Bender Gallery forever.

259
00:14:37,033 --> 00:14:38,967
I want the
Amanda Sloane Gallery.

260
00:14:39,035 --> 00:14:42,095
Not Amanda Weinrib,
'cause there's a euphony problem.

261
00:14:42,171 --> 00:14:46,505
 Three, four, run.
Three, four, and break the ball.

262
00:14:46,575 --> 00:14:48,668
-  Play 88 !
- I hope they don't play like this.

263
00:14:48,744 --> 00:14:50,837
- 88 ! Ten-hut !

264
00:14:50,913 --> 00:14:52,847
What's the matter ?
You seem down.

265
00:14:52,915 --> 00:14:55,440
- No, I'm fine.
- You're fine ?

266
00:14:55,518 --> 00:14:57,452
Something's on your mind,
Lenny.

267
00:14:57,520 --> 00:15:01,854
 Listen, last night I was
at one of those dinner parties again.

268
00:15:01,924 --> 00:15:04,290
Amanda-- You know,
last week she took me to,

269
00:15:04,360 --> 00:15:06,294
to Le Cirque with the Dorians.

270
00:15:06,362 --> 00:15:10,230
And then last night it was
with the Grossbards on Park Avenue.

271
00:15:10,299 --> 00:15:13,928
And then after that,
we were driving home...

272
00:15:14,003 --> 00:15:15,937
and I don't know
what to say.

273
00:15:16,005 --> 00:15:20,101
It was Saturday night, you know, and we
stopped for a light over on Park Avenue.

274
00:15:20,176 --> 00:15:23,873
I looked out the window
and I see some guy and this pretty girl.

275
00:15:23,946 --> 00:15:26,710
And, you know,
they're walking home and, you know,

276
00:15:26,782 --> 00:15:28,943
the guy's carrying
the Sunday papers.

277
00:15:29,018 --> 00:15:32,476
It looked like they were
having so much fun, you know.

278
00:15:32,555 --> 00:15:34,989
And, you know--
I don't know, l--

279
00:15:35,057 --> 00:15:38,254
I remember how great it
used to be with me and Amanda...

280
00:15:38,327 --> 00:15:40,818
in our first apartment,
you know, how romantic it was.

281
00:15:40,896 --> 00:15:44,263
You know, in those days it was
just a kick shopping together...

282
00:15:44,333 --> 00:15:48,235
or, you know, just walking
the New York streets, you know.

283
00:15:48,304 --> 00:15:51,273
Then when Max came,
everything was so great, you know.

284
00:15:51,340 --> 00:15:53,433
We had such terrific times.

285
00:15:53,509 --> 00:15:58,003
I don't know, it's been so long
since there's been, you know,
the old passion between us.

286
00:15:58,080 --> 00:16:01,447
I don't know, but it was the first time
I had any of those thoughts.

287
00:16:01,517 --> 00:16:04,145
And, you know,
they made me feel nervous.

288
00:16:06,856 --> 00:16:09,586
You weren't too pleasant
this evening.

289
00:16:09,658 --> 00:16:12,957
Why, 'cause I said no about going
to your boss Jerry Bender's house...

290
00:16:13,028 --> 00:16:14,962
- in the Hamptons ?
- I'll be fine.

291
00:16:15,030 --> 00:16:17,123
I don't like the Hamptons. You know,
you used to hate the beach yourself.

292
00:16:17,199 --> 00:16:19,292
Yeah, not the way he lives.
It's private and beautiful.

293
00:16:19,368 --> 00:16:21,632
What are you getting
so angry about ?

294
00:16:21,704 --> 00:16:23,831
- 'Cause you won't come.
- Last time we went, I got a tick.

295
00:16:23,906 --> 00:16:26,966
- A tick ? Oh, wow. Big deal.
- For you, it wasn't a big deal.

296
00:16:27,042 --> 00:16:29,840
- But I took my pants off, I had
a black thing living in my leg.
- Everyone will be there.

297
00:16:29,912 --> 00:16:31,937
For the potential contacts,
I can put up with a few ticks.

298
00:16:32,014 --> 00:16:33,948
I don't-- What contacts ?

299
00:16:34,016 --> 00:16:36,041
You know, it's like you're
an international spy.

300
00:16:36,118 --> 00:16:38,951
- You got contacts all over town.
- I plan to have my own gallery,
and soon.

301
00:16:39,021 --> 00:16:41,649
You've changed unbelievably
over the years.

302
00:16:41,724 --> 00:16:43,658
- Oh, yeah ? You know what, Lenny ?
- You used to hate that.

303
00:16:43,726 --> 00:16:45,990
- People grow. They grow. Some people.
- It's not growth.

304
00:16:46,061 --> 00:16:48,529
You used to hate the beach.
And Jerry Bender has got a crush on you.

305
00:16:48,597 --> 00:16:50,030
What?

306
00:16:50,099 --> 00:16:52,033
- This guy stares at you.
- Oh, no. That's nuts.

307
00:16:52,101 --> 00:16:54,035
- That's seriously crazy.
- He mentally undresses you.

308
00:16:54,103 --> 00:16:56,037
- That's his normal look.
- It's not his normal look.

309
00:16:56,105 --> 00:16:58,539
- If he looked at me that way
I'd hit him with a brick.
- Okay. Okay, let's--

310
00:16:58,607 --> 00:17:01,269
- Or kiss him on the lips, maybe.
- Let's drop this. Please ?

311
00:17:07,249 --> 00:17:10,616
Well, what do you mean,
you couldn't find it ?

312
00:17:10,686 --> 00:17:12,847
Well, I'm sorry.
You know, it's dark in here...

313
00:17:12,922 --> 00:17:16,289
and l-- you know,
we haven't done it in a while.

314
00:17:16,358 --> 00:17:18,690
- And then you got so angry at me.
- I wasn't angry.

315
00:17:18,761 --> 00:17:21,696
I wasn't angry. You were fumbling
and I was getting out of the mood.

316
00:17:21,764 --> 00:17:25,131
Sorry, I couldn't find it. This--
We haven't been doing it in a while.

317
00:17:25,201 --> 00:17:28,329
- Okay, let's not get into
a whole discussion here.
- I lost my sense of direction.

318
00:17:28,404 --> 00:17:30,338
I'm tired.

319
00:17:30,406 --> 00:17:32,636
Every marriage goes through
valleys and peaks.

320
00:17:32,708 --> 00:17:35,142
- This is like a valley.
- I don't mind going through a valley.

321
00:17:35,211 --> 00:17:38,806
- But I don't want to sink
beneath sea level here.
- Lenny, why rock the boat ?

322
00:17:38,881 --> 00:17:42,146
You got a bright, beautiful wife.
You got a kid that you're crazy for.

323
00:17:42,218 --> 00:17:44,152
I'm not gonna rock the boat.
Did I tell you about Max ?

324
00:17:44,220 --> 00:17:46,984
They want to put him in a special class
because he's got a high IQ.

325
00:17:47,056 --> 00:17:49,149
Yeah, well, two bright parents.
I mean, what do you expect ?

326
00:17:49,225 --> 00:17:51,489
Yeah, whoever they are.
I mean, I still don't know.

327
00:17:51,560 --> 00:17:53,528
It's like raising thoroughbreds.

328
00:17:53,596 --> 00:17:55,689
This kid must come
from good stock.

329
00:17:55,764 --> 00:17:58,824
He's good-looking; he's got a high IQ;
he's got a great personality.

330
00:17:58,901 --> 00:18:00,596
And he's amusing.

331
00:18:00,669 --> 00:18:02,864
This is not my doing.
Amanda did the whole adoption.

332
00:18:02,938 --> 00:18:05,099
I just resisted.
I complained, like a jerk.

333
00:18:05,174 --> 00:18:09,110
I mean, a good father, a dynamite mother
produces a kid like Max.

334
00:18:09,178 --> 00:18:11,612
I think the father's dead,
you know.

335
00:18:13,349 --> 00:18:16,944
- The mother ?

336
00:18:18,687 --> 00:18:20,621
Don't go any further !

337
00:18:20,689 --> 00:18:22,782
I know what you're thinking,
Lenny, and forget it.

338
00:18:22,858 --> 00:18:25,691
How can I forget it ?
The thought's been put into my head.

339
00:18:25,761 --> 00:18:29,754
Oh, cursed fate. Certain thoughts
are better left unthunk.

340
00:18:29,832 --> 00:18:32,323
I'll bet this kid
has a dynamite mother.

341
00:18:32,401 --> 00:18:35,131
What makes you think he didn't
inherit everything from his father ?

342
00:18:35,204 --> 00:18:37,832
Everything ? That's very unlikely.
But I'm gonna find out.

343
00:18:37,906 --> 00:18:40,136
Let sleeping dogs lie.

344
00:18:40,209 --> 00:18:43,804
- I'll bet she's great.
- Curiosity. That's what kills us.

345
00:18:43,879 --> 00:18:47,315
Not muggers or all that bullshit
about the ozone layer.
It's our own hearts and minds.

346
00:18:47,383 --> 00:18:51,820
- I'm gonna find out.
- Please, Lenny, don't be a schmuck.

347
00:18:51,887 --> 00:18:57,052
I remember the adoption vaguely because
I'm somewhat friendly with Amanda.

348
00:18:57,126 --> 00:18:59,492
But it was not that long ago
that we-- that we did it.

349
00:18:59,561 --> 00:19:02,587
I recall trying to
expedite matters for her.

350
00:19:02,665 --> 00:19:07,227
I somehow think it was
a single parent with no father.

351
00:19:07,303 --> 00:19:10,830
Right. Exactly. So-So how--
Is it possible for me to get the name--

352
00:19:10,906 --> 00:19:12,840
I'd like the name
of the mother, if I could.

353
00:19:12,908 --> 00:19:14,876
That remains forever
in our files.

354
00:19:14,943 --> 00:19:18,902
Even if I have it, I can't give it
to you. May I ask why you want to know ?

355
00:19:18,981 --> 00:19:20,915
Yes, 'cause l-l--
I'm curious about it...

356
00:19:20,983 --> 00:19:23,451
and I'm trying to get
all the information that I can.

357
00:19:23,519 --> 00:19:26,977
- So, so--
- I'm sorry. That's all
I can help you with.

358
00:19:27,056 --> 00:19:29,286
There's no possibility
of, uh--

359
00:19:29,358 --> 00:19:32,122
- No, those are the rules.
- I don't understand.
I'm the father of the child.

360
00:19:32,194 --> 00:19:36,062
- I can't find out who--
- They're very firm. It's never done.

361
00:19:36,131 --> 00:19:38,793
- Mm-hmm.
- How is the little boy doing ?

362
00:19:38,867 --> 00:19:41,131
- Good. He's great. He's fabulous.
- Yes ?

363
00:19:41,203 --> 00:19:44,297
- Yes.
- Say hello to Amanda.

364
00:19:44,373 --> 00:19:47,774
- There's no possibility that I could--
- I'm sorry.

365
00:19:47,843 --> 00:19:51,040
- There's--
- Really sorry. No way.

366
00:19:51,113 --> 00:19:54,139
- Okay, thank you. Thank you.
- Bye-bye.

367
00:20:58,547 --> 00:21:00,515
What are you doing, Weinrib ?

368
00:21:00,582 --> 00:21:03,142
Don't confuse me !
She's coming back in a minute.

369
00:21:03,218 --> 00:21:06,585
- You are breaking the law.
- Breaking the law ?
There's a higher law.

370
00:21:06,655 --> 00:21:09,215
I can find out
who my son's mother is.

371
00:21:09,291 --> 00:21:11,384
The judge won't see it
that way.

372
00:21:11,460 --> 00:21:13,826
Keep a lookout for me,
will you, for Christ's sake ?

373
00:21:13,896 --> 00:21:16,956
- Me? I'm the leader of the Chorus.
- So what? Look out.

374
00:21:17,032 --> 00:21:18,966
Get your friend Bud
to help you.

375
00:21:19,034 --> 00:21:21,559
Bud can't help me. You know,
Ellie and Amanda are friendly.

376
00:21:21,637 --> 00:21:24,663
- Bud can't keep a secret.
- Why is it a secret ?
Why can't Amanda know ?

377
00:21:24,740 --> 00:21:26,867
What kind of argument am I
getting into with you ? Amanda--

378
00:21:26,942 --> 00:21:28,876
'Cause she wouldn't understand.

379
00:21:28,944 --> 00:21:31,003
Oh, you're guilty because you
already have exaggerated notions...

380
00:21:31,079 --> 00:21:33,013
about your son's mother.

381
00:21:33,081 --> 00:21:36,448
It's understandable because things
are not going smoothly with Amanda.

382
00:21:36,518 --> 00:21:39,180
That's why you will always
be a chorus member.

383
00:21:39,254 --> 00:21:41,518
Because you don't do anything.
I act.

384
00:21:41,590 --> 00:21:43,785
I take action.
I make things happen.

385
00:21:43,859 --> 00:21:46,293
Well, hurry the hell up.
I hear footsteps.

386
00:21:50,165 --> 00:21:53,999
I-l forgot my-- I dropped
my manila envelope. I didn't realize it.

387
00:21:54,069 --> 00:21:56,537
- Oh.
- It has an important interview in it.

388
00:21:56,605 --> 00:21:58,573
With-- With Roberto Duran.

389
00:22:01,977 --> 00:22:05,071
You won't believe this,
but he's heading for Pennsylvania.

390
00:22:05,147 --> 00:22:07,138
Of all the human weaknesses,

391
00:22:07,216 --> 00:22:11,118
- obsession is the most dangerous.
-  And the silliest.

392
00:22:12,955 --> 00:22:15,822
- Yeah ?
- I'm looking for a former tenant here,

393
00:22:15,891 --> 00:22:18,325
- a-a-a Leslie Wright.
- Who are you ?

394
00:22:18,393 --> 00:22:20,588
I'm a friend of hers, and I believe
she lived here at one time--

395
00:22:20,662 --> 00:22:22,596
a Leslie Wright ?

396
00:22:22,664 --> 00:22:24,928
Oh, yeah, yeah. I remember
the girl who used to live here.

397
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:26,934
- You remember.
The pretty one upstairs.
- Yeah, yeah, right.

398
00:22:27,002 --> 00:22:29,402
She was only here for a while.
Who are you ?

399
00:22:29,471 --> 00:22:32,065
Uh, I'm just an old friend of hers
and I was trying to track her down.

400
00:22:32,140 --> 00:22:34,165
Do you know-- Do you know
where I could find her ?

401
00:22:34,243 --> 00:22:37,178
Leslie Wailes was her name,
not Leslie Wright. Leslie Wailes.

402
00:22:37,246 --> 00:22:39,180
- Leslie Wailes ?
- Wailes.

403
00:22:39,248 --> 00:22:41,682
- She moved to New York.
- You sure? 'Cause I have Leslie Wright.

404
00:22:41,750 --> 00:22:44,275
Leslie-- Leslie--
Did she get married or--

405
00:22:44,353 --> 00:22:46,378
I don't know.

406
00:22:46,455 --> 00:22:49,424
You have no other information ?
You don't know where I could
find her or anything ?

407
00:22:49,491 --> 00:22:51,925
No. She was only here
for a little while. I told you.

408
00:22:51,994 --> 00:22:54,326
Look, let me give you
my phone number.

409
00:22:54,396 --> 00:22:57,331
If anything turns up,
I would love to locate her.

410
00:23:01,203 --> 00:23:04,195
- Here. Give me that. I'll take that.
- Thank you.

411
00:23:04,273 --> 00:23:06,798
- Yeah. Okay.
- You're welcome.

412
00:23:08,477 --> 00:23:11,810
You have a phone call. Mr. Lamont.
Says he's from Philadelphia.

413
00:23:11,880 --> 00:23:13,814
- Oh.
- You gave him your number ?

414
00:23:13,882 --> 00:23:16,646
- Mm-hmm.
-  ls this Lenny Weinrib ?

415
00:23:16,718 --> 00:23:18,652
- Go ahead, sir.
- Hello.

416
00:23:18,720 --> 00:23:22,053
Yeah, this is Bill Lamont.
Um, that woman you were looking for--

417
00:23:22,124 --> 00:23:25,719
We asked another guy who said
her name was Leslie St. James.

418
00:23:25,794 --> 00:23:28,922
Said she moved to New York City,
talked about becoming an actress.

419
00:23:28,997 --> 00:23:31,431
- Leslie St. James ?
- Yes, sir. Yeah.

420
00:23:31,500 --> 00:23:36,301
He remembered her quite well.
Leslie St. James is the name she took.

421
00:23:36,371 --> 00:23:41,832
There was a Leslie St. James who was
a member of the Screen Extras Guild.

422
00:23:41,910 --> 00:23:44,071
- So that's that.
- So what are you telling me ?

423
00:23:44,146 --> 00:23:47,912
That-- That she was a movie
extra or stage extra ?

424
00:23:47,983 --> 00:23:50,110
Yeah.
That's all I have.

425
00:23:50,185 --> 00:23:52,244
So-- And there's an address,
but, uh, you know,

426
00:23:52,321 --> 00:23:55,757
this book's
a few years old. So.

427
00:23:55,824 --> 00:23:58,019
I'm looking for a--
it's-- she--

428
00:23:58,093 --> 00:24:00,891
A Leslie St. James
or maybe it's a Leslie Wailes.

429
00:24:00,963 --> 00:24:03,397
- I don't know,
but I think she lived here.
- Oh, yeah, sure. I remember.

430
00:24:03,465 --> 00:24:06,866
She was a tall girl.
